cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a natural language generation (NLG) task in the context of computational storytelling systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques (LSTM Encoder-Decoder networks) for the NLG task. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves training a neural network on a large dataset (WikiLarge) to generate semantically equivalent text with increased complexity. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of a corpus of computationally generated stories (Compiled Computer Tales) to test the capabilities of the NLG system. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category, but relevant as the paper involves training a neural network for the NLG task.
